  <titles>
    <title type="display">Honest and Open Testimony Act</title>
    <title type="official" as="introduced">To amend title 10, United States Code, to include the disclosure of sexual orientation by a member of the Armed Forces to a Member of Congress as a lawful and protected communication and to prohibit retaliatory personnel actions against members of the Armed Forces who make such a disclosure in a Congressional hearing or who testify, for or against, the policy concerning homosexuality in the Armed Forces.</title>
    <title type="short" as="introduced">Honest and Open Testimony Act</title>
  </titles>
